s a yellow LED light.";i:13;s:23:"The yellow light shows.";i:14;s:80:"Its only about a year old and when I use my remote it blinks red and wont close.";i:15;s:19:"High School or GED.";i:16;s:60:"One of my garage door sensors is solid yellow and the other.";i:17;s:46:"One of my garage door sensors is solid yellow.";i:18;s:80:"One photo eye will have an Amber LED Yellow and the other will have a green LED.";i:19;s:74:"The transmitting photo eye has the yellow LED and it should always be lit.";i:20;s:69:"When it is lit it is sending the beam across the garage door opening.";i:21;s:48:"If it is off none of the photo eyes will be lit.";i:22;s:171:"The yellow light of garage door sensors is mostly seen in the sending sensor this helps to transmit the infrared beam to the receiving sensor that has a green light on it.";i:23;s:52:"The green light sensor is always supposed to be lit.";i:24;s:151:"Chamberlain LiftMaster and Sears Craftsman garage door openers manufactured after 1997 will have an amber or yellow light on the sending safety sensor.";i:25;s:97:"The light on the sending sensor should always be on even if the sensors are not aligned properly.";i:26;s:65:"I have one sensor with a green light and one with a yellow light.";i:27;s:20:"What does that mean.";i:28;s:23:"July 17 2020 at 103 am.";i:29;s:100:"My garage door sensor red light is out but the green light is on yet the garage door does not close.";i:30;s:74:"Do I need to buy a new sensor or do I simply need to adjust the alignment.";i:31;s:27:"Leave a Reply Cancel reply.";i:32;s:108:"Garage door sensors utilize a photo-eye sensor and a beam of infrared light that goes between the two units.";i:33;s:71:"The units are placed near the ground on either side of the garage door.";i:34;s:105:"If the beam of light is interrupted while the garage door is closing the door will stop and rise back up.";i:35;s:262:"Liftmaster Garage Door Opener Yellow Light Blinking Posted on June 14 2020 by Bandi Ruma Wall mount wi fi garag